  "prompt": "What should be India's national game?",
  "response": "India does not have an officially designated national game. However, hockey is often regarded as the de facto national sport due to its historical significance and achievements, particularly during the mid-20th century when India won several Olympic gold medals. \n\nCricket, on the other hand, is currently the most popular and widely followed sport in India. It enjoys immense popularity, significant media coverage, and has a huge fan base, making it the dominant sport in the country today.\n\nDetermining what should be India's national game can be subjective and might depend on various factors such as historical achievements, current popularity, and cultural impact. Ultimately, it would be up to the government or relevant authorities to decide, keeping in mind the sentiments and preferences of the Indian population.",
